          "The imperative mood (-u) is used for commands,",
          "requests, and wishes. It's the same for all",
          "subjects - no conjugation needed!",
          "",
          "FORMING COMMANDS:",
          "Change -i (infinitive) to -u (imperative):",
          "veni → Venu!       = Come!",
          "manĝi → Manĝu!     = Eat!",
          "rigardi → Rigardu! = Look!",
          "helpi → Helpu min! = Help me!",
          "",
          "POLITE REQUESTS:",
          "Bonvolu sidiĝi.   = Please sit down.",
          "Atentu!           = Pay attention!",
          "",
          "FOR ALL SUBJECTS:",
          "Ni iru!   = Let's go! (we)",
          "Li venu.  = Let him come. (he)",
          "",
          "Commands are simple: just change -i to -u!"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Leciono tridek"
